        {
          "type": "tip",
          "title": "🔄 The Dutch number flip",
          "text": "After 20, units come BEFORE tens with 'en' (and):\n\n21 — eenentwintig (1 and 20)\n32 — tweeëndertig (2 and 30)\n45 — vijfenveertig (5 and 40)\n67 — zevenenzestig (7 and 60)\n88 — achtentachtig (8 and 80)\n99 — negenennegentig (9 and 90)\n\nIt sounds complex but Dutch children learn it effortlessly — you will too!\n\n🔢 Full tens:\n20 twintig · 30 dertig · 40 veertig · 50 vijftig\n60 zestig · 70 zeventig · 80 tachtig · 90 negentig"
        },
